> nit-pick: is this really a timeout? In that case you would have used
> wait_for_completion_timeout(), no?

With respects to the xHCI command implementation, every time a command is queued to the host controller, it arms timer (xhci->cmd_timer) that is used to handle the timeout conditions.Â  This is the reason for not using the _timeout() variant, as we can let the xHCI command timeout handler do the cleanup and stopping of the HCD. (marking as dead)Â  It will also ensure that any completion events are completed as part of the timeout handler as well (xhci_handle_command_timeout() --> xhci_abort_cmd_ring())

Thanks

Wesley Cheng

